    ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ


@ENDNODE

@NODE 6. "Template"

    WhatDir FILES/M,INFO/S,COMMENT/S,FORCECOM/S,COLS/N/K,NOSIZE/S,
            LISTALL/S,OWNER/S,??/S

    FILES/M             One or more file(s) or directories. May
                        contain wildcards!

    INFO/S              Show additional info about file, date etc.
                        And info about picture size etc. if it's
                        a picture.

    COMMENT/S           Should WhatDir comment all files with its
                        filetype? (Default=Off)

    FORCECOM/S          Should WhatDir also comment not recognized
                        files which WhatDir only shows how many
                        percents of the file which is Ascii chars.
                        (WhatDir doesn't comment those by default, to
                        keep any old filecomment.) Use this in
                        conjuction with the COMMENT option.

    COLS/N/K            Is used to determine after how many characters
                        WhatDir will cut of. If you are using a very
                        small window, you should set this to a value
                        that suits you. And if you're using a very
                        big window (SuperHires etc), you may set this
                        to higher values. Currently only accepts
                        values between 40 and 100. Although current
                        version contains no filetype strings that
                        won't fit with about 90 cols.
                        You may set this if you can't see all the
                        description.  (Default value = 76)
                        Please note that setting this value doesn't
                        cutoff filecomments when using COMMENT!

    NOSIZE/S            This will suppress the showing of the filelength.

    LISTALL/S           This will list all filetypes that current version
                        of WhatDir recognizes. (sorry, but not in alpha-
                        order)

    OWNER/S             Show owner of the file. In V39+ (3.0) filesystems
                        can keep the name of the fileowner. This is usefull
                        for NetWorks etc. Owner consists of two fields:
                        Group Id (4 letters) & User Id (4 letters), how this
                        should be use haven't been defined by Commodore (yet).
                        But currently the filesystems doesn't care about it.
                        This will also show the protection bits for the
                        Group/User.
                        I CAN'T GUARANTE THAT THIS OPTION WORKS CORRECTLY.

    ??                  Show help text.



    Please refer to any AmigaDos 2.0 Reference for more information
    about Templates and modifiers.



@ENDNODE

@NODE 7. "Examples"

    (1)  1.dh0:> WhatDir #?.info COMMENT

         This will comment all files in dh0: ending with '.info'
         (ie icons) with their filetypes.


    (2)  1.dh0:> WhatDir df0:Strange INFO

         This will check the file 'Strange' in device 'df0:' and
         show all info about it. It may look like this:

         FileInfo
        
            File         : StrangePic
            DirEntryType : -3
            Protect      : ----RW-D
            Size         : 34456
            Date         : 14:29:20, Today (Sunday)
            FileComment  : 

         Type

            GIF v87a Picture (.gif)           

            Width          : 60 pixels
            Height         : 45 pixels
            Bitplanes      : 8
            ColorBits      : 8 colorbits/pixel
            Background Col : 0
            Global ColorMap: Yes              



    (3)  1.dh0:> WhatDir #?

         This will check all files in current directory (in this case
         is current directory 'dh0:'). It may look like this.

         Painting.PIC       12144 : VideoShow PIC Picture (.PIC)
         Car.SCD             4780 : Scodl Picture (.SCD)    
         Times.AFM          40212 : Adobe Metric Font (.afm)
         Others             <DIR> : Directory
         Moon               16420 : Iff: ILBM - Interleaved Bit Map (Picture)
         Moon.info           2324 : Project Icon (.info)
         PacMan             94296 : Executable
         PacMan.hiscore       152 : ±  78 % Ascii chars   1)
         Pictures.ARJ       21588 : Arj Archive (.arj)

         1) = If WhatDir can't recognize a file, it will just show how
              many percents of the file which are Asciichars. Please
              keep in mind that it doesn't classify foreign chars
              as Ascii (ĺäçř...).



    (4)  1.dh0:> WhatDir dh0:1 dh0:data#? NOSIZE

         This will cause WhatDir to check the file/dir '1' in 'dh0:'
         and all files beginning with 'data' (for example will 'data.iff'
         be matched but not 'gamedata'). WhatDir will not show the file
         lenght.



@ENDNODE

@NODE 8. "HunkAnalyzer"

      If you use the option INFO when you check an executable file, WhatDir
    will view the hunkstructure. WhatDir doesn't support all hunks yet...



@ENDNODE

@NODE 9. "IffAnalyzer"

      If you use the option INFO when you check an iff file, WhatDir will
    view all chunks in the file. WhatDir doesn't recognize 'advanced' iff
    types as CAT & PREP.

      WhatDir will display some more info about some iff-chunks, the size
    of a picture and much much more.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 10. "File-/LinkViruses"

      Whenever you list a executable file, WhatDir will check if the file
    contains any file or link virus. Currently WhatDir doesn't recognize
    so many link/fileviruses but it will increase in the future.
      If WhatDir finds a link virus it will just warn you about it. It
    can't kill it. You must use a viruskiller to kill the virus (eg BootX
    by Peter Stuer).



@ENDNODE

@NODE 11. "Tips about Usage"

      The whole project started when I was working on a directory
    handlingprogram (a la DirectoryOpus), but when newer versions
    of DirOpus occured which had all functions I was about to make
    in my program I gave up and made it an CLI program, no intuition
    interface.
      It's smart to use WhatDir in conjunction with DirOpus, here is
    two gadgets to use in DirOpus (v3.51+).


    WhatDir                           WdComment

    Executable   WhatDir {F}          Executable   WhatDir {F} COMMENT

    Flags:  Output window             Flags:  Recursive directories
            Recursive directories             Rescan source

    CloseDelay: -1


      The first gadget will simply list all selected files (in the
    source) and after that ask you to press the left mousebutton.

      The second gadget will comment all selected files to what
    filetype they are. This allows you to see it from diropus always.


    - Directory Opus is Copyrighted by Jonathan Potter 1990-92 -
                  - Published by INOVAtronics -



@ENDNODE

@NODE 12. "Why is WhatDir best?"

      Many of you have probably seen many other filetype listers, and
    now comes WhatDir. But WhatDir isn't just another filetype lister,
    it's much better here is some of the reasons:

    · It doesn't just look at the extension (as FileType by Mattias Pĺlsson
      does to recognize Many of it's filetypes). Why? If someone has renamed
      the file it will show the wrong filetype (could you guess that?).

    · It recognizes more filetypes than any other lister (WhatIs v2.5 by
      J.Tyberghein recognizes about 100 filetypes, FileType v1.20 by
      Mattias Pĺlsson recognizes about 150 filetypes but about half of
      them is recognized by the filename buuuuh :-/ )

    · WhatDir is much faster than all other recognizers available. In
      a test against WhatIs, was WhatDir 1.5 times faster than WhatIs!!
      Some other tests has showed slightly better and some has showed
      slightly slower results. But WhatDir is always the fastest and
      most powerfull filelister!

    · Has many functions: Filetype recognizer, hunkanalyzer,
      iff analyzer & file-/linkviruschecker.



@ENDNODE

